                    <item>
              <title>Using twitter for language learning</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/925</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/925</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>
<a href="http://twitter.com">Twitter</a> is a microblogging tool. You can post ('tweet') messages up to 140 characters. You follow people and people follow you. The tweets appear as a continuous stream. This <a href="http://www.commoncraft.com/Twitter">creativecommons</a> video gives you a good summary of Twitter and how it can be used. 
</p>
<p>
&nbsp;
</p>
<p>
I have found it really useful to use this as a means of helping my Spanish language learning. I am now following a number of Spanish speakers and find the constant drip of Spanish tweets a useful means of reinforcing my learning. In addition I have used Twitter as a means of seeking help. For example last year I tweeted a query about using Ser or Estar and got three really helpful replies almost immediately.   
</p>
]]></description>
          <pubDate>Mon, 23 Feb 2009 10:49:19 +0000</pubDate>
            </item>
                    <item>
              <title>Using twitter in academia</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/613</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/613</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p>Twitter use has exploded in the last six months or so, to the extent that some are saying</p>
<p>microblogging is the death of blogging. This is a nice article which gives on perspective on the</p>
<p>use of Twitter in an educational context. Also has some nice links to related useful</p>
<p>information.</p>
<p></p>
<p><strong>Here are some of the useful suggestions:</strong></p>
<ul>
    <li>Class chatter</li>
    <li>Classroom community</li>
    <li>Get a sense of the world</li>
    <li>Track a word</li>
    <li>Track a conference</li>
    <li>Instant feedback</li>
    <li>Follow a professional </li>
    <li>Follow a famous person</li>
    <li>Grammar</li>
    <li>Rule based writing </li>
    <li>Maximising the teaching moment</li>
    <li>Public notepad</li>
    <li>Writing assignments</li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<p>Form <a href="http://academhack.outsidethetext.com/home/">acadamHacK</a> blog</p>
<p></p>
<p></p>
<p></p>
<p></p>]]></description>
